node.text: @juau_alt wow this is new to me 😊

Built in the early 1900s, these iconic shophouses with intricate Oriental designs and Peranakan motifs have carefully conserved as part of an island-wide initiative to preserve this Southeast Asian island country's colorful history.
@howdy_lhouvum thank you for leaving a comment 😊
@jeffreysiow admire them for playing a part to aid the conservation efforts!
@chief_curator it’s by law, so they’ve to compliant😅 In actual fact, only the exterior facade need to be maintained. The interiors are mostly renovated to individual owner’s taste.
I’ve a friend living one of these houses, very near to the ones in the pic. But hers doesn’t have a private front yard.
@ferinadb you can find them in the Joo Chiat and Katong areas!
@chief_curator thanks a lot for your info😊🙏🏻

What island is it? So refined and beautiful 😍
